- Sprint goals were documented in Trello
- The Sprint 2 planning report was completed and pushed to GitHub
- Sprint 2 team meetings were conducted, and an agreed method for tracking individual working hours was established.

## Demo Summary (What Was Shown in the Review)

## What Went Well

- Good communication between team members
- Clear initial project setup
- Effective use of Trello for task organization
- Early preparation of planning artifacts by the Scrum Master supported efficient teamwork
- Active participation from team members in backlog creation and discussion

## What Could Be Improved

Sometimes team members weren't as attentive as they could have been.

## Next Sprint Focus

- Planning for Sprint 3
- Coding the MVP
- Trello update

